Basani Baloyi was fired for lacking the required skills and conduct for the position of Chief Operations Officer. JOHANNESBURG - The Public Protector is facing another court battle. This time from someone who used to work in her office. Basani Baloyi was fired for lacking the required skills and conduct for the position of Chief Operations Officer. READ: Parliament pondering rules on removal of Public Protector But she's challenging her dismissal and wants the North Gauteng High Court to declare that Busisiwe Mkhwebane abused her office and violated the constitution. The former chief operating officer at the Public Protector's office, Basani Baloyi is fighting for her job back.